The paper deals with optimization problems and spectral decomposition of matrices, which are topics that are commonly studied in computer science. The use of graph limit theory and pseudorandomness also suggests a connection to theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
